5. We ſhould remember our Dangers, with conſideration to the frequency of them, how frequently we were in them. Paul remember'd this, in Perils by Sea often, in Perils by the Heathens, &c. (2 Cor. 11.26.) O how often have we been near Drowning, near Taking, near Sinking, near Dying, and yet God brought us off; theſe things we ſhould call to mind often who go out upon dangerous Voyages, and often come home; 
                  •
               he oftner and more frequent our dangers, the more ſhould we think upon them.
